Revision history for Array::Columnize

1.04 2013-06-12
    - botched release 1.03

1.03 2013-06-12
    - Add linesuffix, and colfmt options
    - document all options
    - Work around rlib limitation.

1.02 2012-08-19
    - Rerelease just for some Meta and Doc changes

1.01 2012-08-13
    - Add option arrange_array to format as an array.
    - Use rlib more pervasivly and use it
    - incompatible change: always end string with "\n"

1.00 2012-08-12
    - Packaging changes. Version number conforms to
      http://perldoc.perl.org/perlmodstyle.html#Version-numbering
    - Change Meta data to point to github repository and issue tracker

0.4.2 2012-01-02
    - Re-release to reduce dependencies

0.4.1 2011-12-03
    - Try to silence CPANTS

0.4.0 2011-11-24
    - Handle situations where text is longer than display width.
    - More strict on tests and as per CPANTS reports

0.3.9 2011-11-12
    - rerelease with 'dev' in version number.
      it was messing up some Module::Builds
    - Update GNUmakefile
    - Build.PL back to more convenient form (for worse kwalitee).

0.3.8 2011-10-29
    - Made the Build.PL non-executable (for better kwalitee:
        - http://cpants.perl.org/kwalitee.html#buildtool_not_executable
    - Add an environment variable - PERL_MB_NOSIGN to disable signing a package
    (which interferes with the flow of doing ./Build disttest ).
    - Renamed Makefile to Makefile.devel so doing perl Makefile.PL won't
    interfere with it.
    - Correct some typos in the README.md and added a TODO there (SHLOMIF).
    - Add some POD to lib/Array/Columnize.pm (SHLOMIF).

0.3.7 2011-10-28
I said, no feature "say"!

0.3.6 2011-10-27
Remove feature "say" so it works on Perl pre 5.010.

0.3.5 2011-09-05
Initial revision
